  m_Name: Level_14_Tazumal
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  levelNumber: 14
  levelName: Tazumal
  location: Chalchuapa, El Salvador
  levelDescription: "Where towering pyramids rose above Chalchuapa, Tazumal kept
    the fire of Maya ceremony alive.\n\nTazumal, located in Chalchuapa, western El
    Salvador, is one of the most important Maya sites in the country. Its name means
    \u201CThe place where souls are burned\u201D in K\u2019iche\u2019 Maya. The city
    flourished between 100 AD and 1200 AD, serving as a ceremonial and trade center
    connected to wider Mesoamerican networks.\r\n\r\nThe site\u2019s centerpiece
    is a stepped pyramid rising over 24 meters, the largest in El Salvador. Excavations
    revealed burials, offerings, and evidence of rituals, including incense burners
    and jade ornaments. Tazumal also shows influence from distant cultures\u2014its
    ballcourt and architectural style reflect ties with central Mexico.\r\n\r\nLater,
    during the Postclassic period, Tazumal remained active until the Spanish conquest,
    after which the structures were partly dismantled and reused. Today, the ruins
    stand as a reminder of El Salvador\u2019s deep Maya heritage, preserved within
    the Chalchuapa Archaeological Zone alongside other nearby sites like Casa Blanca
    and El Trapiche"
  siteImage: {fileID: 21300000, guid: 8ee1d3ccfcb2f7a4184cc3cc8421a9ce, type: 3}
